In addition, intrasubspecific variations occur in the intercercal process (
Figure 4H – J
) and subgenital plate ( Figure 4K, L ). Based on the materials examined, similar intercercal processes are found in different localities, e.g. the form similar to Figure 4H being distributed in different locations of Yunnan (Meng ’ a, Simao, Yangbi). On the contrary, varied intercercal processes could be found at the same locality, e.g. specimens depicted as Figure 4H and 4J are from Meng ’ a, while those depicted as Figure 4I and 4H are both found in Yangbi. The same situation applies for the subgenital plate.
